{"type":"message","id":"ee73ad35","parentId":"f13029c6","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:34:42.581Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_4a3k2yw4r8cx_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 153320\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/HYBRID_SCORING_EXPERIMENT.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best single action.\r\n\r\nFrom the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 (architecture analysis) are COMPLETE\r\n2. Key pending item: **Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)**\r\n   - Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n   - Test whether this distinguishes \"constant format\" (freq≈160, CFI=1) from \"research trajectory\" (freq<120, CFI>0.5)\r\n   - Run: 200 pulses, 80/20 split, compare against binary thresholds\r\n\r\nThe previous experiment (CFI Compression Synthesis) established that:\r\n- CFI ≥ 0.7 AND freq < 60 is TOO aggressive - loses 92.9% recall\r\n- The Constant Format Problem was discovered - tokens like \"for next instantiation\", \"pulse\", \"completed at:\" have CFI=1.00 but freq=160 - they're metaprogramming artifacts\r\n\r\nThe three-dimensional filter identified: CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ≥ 3 AND freq < 120\r\n\r\nThe next step is clear: **Run the hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment**\r\n\r\nThis will test: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nI need to:\r\n1. Create or update the experiment script to implement this scoring\r\n2. Run it on the 200 pulses with 80/20 split\r\n3. Compare against the previous binary thresholds\r\n\r\nLet me look at what already exists. I should check the research directory for the previous experiment to build upon it.\r\n\r\nActually, I should create an experiment script that:\r\n1. Loads the pulse data\r\n2. Calculates score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120) for each token\r\n3. Tests various thresholds on this score\r\n\r\n\r\n4. Compares against the binary threshold results from the previous experiment\r\n\r\nI'll synthesize the experiment results, documenting how the hybrid scoring approach performs against binary thresholds. The script will generate comparative metrics, revealing the effectiveness of the new scoring method in distinguishing research trajectory tokens from constant format artifacts.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI Compression Synthesis established that binary thresholds fail due to the \"Constant Format Problem\" - tokens with CFI=1.0 and freq=160 are metaprogramming artifacts, not research. The next step is to test the hybrid scoring formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120).\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nDesign and implement the hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment to test Strategy C against the previous binary threshold results. This will validate whether the continuous scoring approach can distinguish constant-format tokens (high CFI, high freq) from research trajectory tokens (moderate CFI, moderate freq).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Hybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Experiment (Strategy C)\r\n# Testing: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n# \r\n# Previous findings (CFI Compression Synthesis):\r\n# - Binary thresholds (CFI ≥ 0.7 AND freq < 60) TOO aggressive: +32.9% precision but -92.9% recall\r\n# - Constant Format Problem: tokens with CFI=1.0, freq=160 are metaprogramming artifacts\r\n# - \"Phase 1\" (freq=136, CFI=0.96) is TRUE research trajectory despite high CFI\r\n#\r\n# Hypothesis: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n# - Tokens at freq=120+ get score = CFI (full credit)\r\n# - Tokens at freq<120 get score = CFI × (freq/120) (scaled down)\r\n# - This should DEMOTE constant-format (freq=160, CFI=1.0 → score=1.0) but\r\n#   preserve research tokens (freq=136, CFI=0.96 → score=0.96)\r\n#\r\n# Wait - this doesn't help! If freq=160, score=1.0 still. Need INVERSE freq.\r\n# Revised formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, 120/freq(T))\r\n# - freq=160 → score = 1.0 × 0.75 = 0.75 (demoted!)\r\n# - freq=136 → score = 0.96 × 0.88 = 0.845 (demoted somewhat)\r\n# - freq=60 → score = CFI × 2.0 = capped at 1.0\r\n# - freq=30 → score = CFI × 4.0 = capped at 1.0\r\n#\r\n# EVEN BETTER: penalize HIGH frequency, reward MODERATE frequency\r\n# score(T) = CFI(T) / (1 + α × max(0, freq(T) - threshold))\r\n# Where α controls penalty strength, threshold = optimal freq window center\r\n\r\n# EXPERIMENT DESIGN\r\n# 1. Load pulse data (tokens, CFI, frequency for each)\r\n# 2. Implement: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n# 3. Implement: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, 120/freq(T))  \r\n# 4. Test multiple thresholds: 60, 80, 100, 120 for the freq window\r\n# 5. 80/20 train/test split on 200 pulses\r\n# 6. Compare against baseline (all tokens) and binary thresholds\r\n\r\n# BASELINE COMPARISON\r\n# - Baseline (all tokens): expected ~45% precision (random selection)\r\n\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 15:33:41\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774380882580}}
