{"type":"message","id":"7fb398f4","parentId":"411952a9","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:34:48.488Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_l26i586rrhx5_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 4497\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2844\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] and\r\n[mutation proposed] and\r\n[master 07702e6] pulse: 2026-03-24 153421\n 5 files changed, 313 insertions(+), 67 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 153421.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-24 153421.mutation\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 153421 - The CFI Compression Synthesis identified that the hybrid formula score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120) should distinguish constant-format tokens from research trajectory tokens. This experiment is the next logical step to validate or refine the three-dimensional filter.\r\n\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"grand-valley","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 4497\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2844\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] and\r\n[mutation proposed] and\r\n[master 07702e6] pulse: 2026-03-24 153421\n 5 files changed, 313 insertions(+), 67 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 153421.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-24 153421.mutation\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 153421 - The CFI Compression Synthesis identified that the hybrid formula score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120) should distinguish constant-format tokens from research trajectory tokens. This experiment is the next logical step to validate or refine the three-dimensional filter.\r\n","name":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774380888486}}
{"type":"message","id":"64a3d967","parentId":"7fb398f4","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:34:52.018Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pulse completed successfully. Let me now read the most recent log file and the mutation that was proposed.","thinkingSignature":"ceaed78126aaf6e592cdac72d1178cabf205654bf8e8dde3bf25d24376a1db3e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_q778ia7oup20_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-24 153421.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_q778ia7oup20_2","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\mutations\\proposed\\2026-03-24 153421.mutation"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2113,"output":123,"cacheRead":12245,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14481,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774380888489}}
{"type":"message","id":"709984be","parentId":"64a3d967","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:34:52.031Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_q778ia7oup20_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 153421\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals and insights:\r\n\r\n1. Phase 1 Advancement: CFI Compression Experiment was just completed\r\n2. The next pending experiment is the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n3. Key insight: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nThe most logical next action is to implement and run this hybrid scoring experiment. I should:\r\n1. Create a new script to test the hybrid scoring formula\r\n2. Run it on the same 200 pulses\r\n3. Compare results against the binary thresholds (CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120))\r\n\r\nLet me check what exists:\r\n- I have pulse data in research/ directory\r\n- I need to run the hybrid experiment\r\n\r\nI'll create a Python script to perform this experiment and run it. This advances the immediate pending task.\r\n\r\nActually, I should create a script that:\r\n1. Loads the 200 pulses\r\n2. Applies both scoring methods\r\n3. Compares precision/recall\r\n4. Outputs results\r\n\r\nLet me create the experiment script and run it.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI Compression Synthesis identified that the hybrid formula score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120) should distinguish constant-format tokens from research trajectory tokens. This experiment is the next logical step to validate or refine the three-dimensional filter.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate and execute the hybrid scoring experiment script to compare Strategy C (continuous scoring) against the binary threshold approach on the 200-pulse corpus.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nHybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Experiment\r\nStrategy C: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nCompares against binary threshold (CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120))\r\n\"\"\"\r\nimport json\r\nimport math\r\nfrom collections import defaultdict\r\n\r\n# Load pulse data\r\nwith open('state/pulses/pulses.json', 'r') as f:\r\n    pulses = json.load(f)\r\n\r\n# Build token frequency and co-occurrence counts\r\ntoken_freq = defaultdict(int)\r\nco_occur = defaultdict(lambda: defaultdict(int))\r\ntotal_pairs = 0\r\n\r\nfor pulse in pulses:\r\n    tokens = pulse['tokens']\r\n    for t in tokens:\r\n        token_freq[t] += 1\r\n    for i in range(len(tokens)):\r\n        for j in range(i+1, min(i+5, len(tokens))):\r\n            co_occur[tokens[i]][tokens[j]] += 1\r\n            total_pairs += 1\r\n\r\n# Calculate CFI for each token\r\ndef calc_cfi(token):\r\n    if token_freq[token] == 0:\r\n        return 0.0\r\n    co_count = sum(co_occur[token].values())\r\n    co_prob = co_count / total_pairs if total_pairs > 0 else 0\r\n    freq_prob = token_freq[token] / sum(token_freq.values())\r\n    return min(1.0, co_prob / freq_prob) if freq_prob > 0 else 0.0\r\n\r\ncfi_scores = {t: calc_cfi(t) for t in token_freq}\r\n\r\n# Strategy A: Binary threshold (CFI >= 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120))\r\ndef strategy_a(token):\r\n    return 1 if (cfi_scores[token] >= 0.5 and 3 <= token_freq[token] < 120) else 0\r\n\r\n# Strategy C: Hybrid scoring\r\ndef strategy_c(token):\r\n    freq = token_freq[token]\r\n    cfi = cfi_scores[token]\r\n    return cfi * min(1.0, freq / 120)\r\n\r\n# Calculate relevance signal (freq correlates with importance)\r\nrelevance = {t: min(1.0, f/120) for t, f in token_freq.items()}\r\n\r\n# Evaluate on held-out validation set (last 40 pulses)\r\nval_pulses = pulses[160:]\r\nval_tokens = [t for p in val_pulses for t in p['tokens']]\r\n\r\n# Binary filter: true positive if token appears in validation AND passes filter\r\nbinary_tp = sum(1 for t in val_tokens if strategy_a(t) == 1)\r\nbinary_total_filtered = sum(1 for t in set(val_tokens) if strategy_a(t) == 1)\r\nbinary_precision = binary_tp / binary_total_filtered if binary_total_filtered > 0 else 0\r\n\r\n# Hybrid scores for validation tokens\r\nhybrid_scores = {t: strategy_c(t) for t in set(val_tokens)}\r\ntop_k = int(len(hybrid_scores) * 0.2)  # Top 20%\r\ntop_tokens = sorted(hybrid_scores.items(), key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)[:top_k]\r\nhybrid_recall = sum(1 for t, _ in top_tokens if t in val_tokens) / len(set(val_tokens))\r\n\r\n# Key distinction test\r\nconstant_tokens = [t for t, f in token_freq.items() if f >= 150 and cfi_scores[t] >= 0.95]\r\nresearch_tokens = [t for t, f in token_freq.items() if 3 <= f < 120 and cfi_scores[t] >= 0.5]\r\n\r\nconst_a_scores = [(t, strategy_a(t), strategy_c(t)) for t in constant_tokens[:10]]\r\nresearch_a_scores = [(t, strategy_a(t), strategy_c(t)) for t in research_tokens[:10]]\r\n\r\nprint(\"=\" * 60)\r\nprint(\"HYBRID CFI×Freq SCORING EXPERIMENT RESULTS\")\r\nprint(\"=\" * 60)\r\nprint(f\"\\nBinary Precision (\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 15:34:41\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774380892028}}
{"type":"message","id":"84c7a68f","parentId":"709984be","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:34:52.034Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_q778ia7oup20_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"and\n---\n[NEW_FILE]\n---\n#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nHybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Experiment\nStrategy C: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\n\nCompares against binary threshold (CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120))\n\"\"\"\nimport json\nimport math\nfrom collections import defaultdict\n\n# Load pulse data\nwith open('state/pulses/pulses.json', 'r') as f:\n    pulses = json.load(f)\n\n# Build token frequency and co-occurrence counts\ntoken_freq = defaultdict(int)\nco_occur = defaultdict(lambda: defaultdict(int))\ntotal_pairs = 0\n\nfor pulse in pulses:\n    tokens = pulse['tokens']\n    for t in tokens:\n        token_freq[t] += 1\n    for i in range(len(tokens)):\n        for j in range(i+1, min(i+5, len(tokens))):\n            co_occur[tokens[i]][tokens[j]] += 1\n            total_pairs += 1\n\n# Calculate CFI for each token\ndef calc_cfi(token):\n    if token_freq[token] == 0:\n        return 0.0\n    co_count = sum(co_occur[token].values())\n    co_prob = co_count / total_pairs if total_pairs > 0 else 0\n    freq_prob = token_freq[token] / sum(token_freq.values())\n    return min(1.0, co_prob / freq_prob) if freq_prob > 0 else 0.0\n\ncfi_scores = {t: calc_cfi(t) for t in token_freq}\n\n# Strategy A: Binary threshold (CFI >= 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120))\ndef strategy_a(token):\n    return 1 if (cfi_scores[token] >= 0.5 and 3 <= token_freq[token] < 120) else 0\n\n# Strategy C: Hybrid scoring\ndef strategy_c(token):\n    freq = token_freq[token]\n    cfi = cfi_scores[token]\n    return cfi * min(1.0, freq / 120)\n\n# Calculate relevance signal (freq correlates with importance)\nrelevance = {t: min(1.0, f/120) for t, f in token_freq.items()}\n\n# Evaluate on held-out validation set (last 40 pulses)\nval_pulses = pulses[160:]\nval_tokens = [t for p in val_pulses for t in p['tokens']]\n\n# Binary filter: true positive if token appears in validation AND passes filter\nbinary_tp = sum(1 for t in val_tokens if strategy_a(t) == 1)\nbinary_total_filtered = sum(1 for t in set(val_tokens) if strategy_a(t) == 1)\nbinary_precision = binary_tp / binary_total_filtered if binary_total_filtered > 0 else 0\n\n# Hybrid scores for validation tokens\nhybrid_scores = {t: strategy_c(t) for t in set(val_tokens)}\ntop_k = int(len(hybrid_scores) * 0.2)  # Top 20%\ntop_tokens = sorted(hybrid_scores.items(), key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)[:top_k]\nhybrid_recall = sum(1 for t, _ in top_tokens if t in val_tokens) / len(set(val_tokens))\n\n# Key distinction test\nconstant_tokens = [t for t, f in token_freq.items() if f >= 150 and cfi_scores[t] >= 0.95]\nresearch_tokens = [t for t, f in token_freq.items() if 3 <= f < 120 and cfi_scores[t] >= 0.5]\n\nconst_a_scores = [(t, strategy_a(t), strategy_c(t)) for t in constant_tokens[:10]]\nresearch_a_scores = [(t, strategy_a(t), strategy_c(t)) for t in research_tokens[:10]]\n\nprint(\"=\" * 60)\nprint(\"HYBRID CFI×Freq SCORING EXPERIMENT RESULTS\")\nprint(\"=\" * 60)\nprint(f\"\\nBinary Precision (\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774380892032}}
